2022 was so wild that I almost forgot we threw Nerf footballs around Amen Corner 🤯. We also:

🚀 Sent Coby to outer space

🏈 Hosted a Thursday Night Football alternate broadcast for four NFL games

🎟️ Sold out NBA arenas on a nationwide summer tour

🏀 Filmed a YouTube video with Luka

🎢 Announced a new $100M+ Dude Perfect theme park & HQ

🏟️ Visited every World Cup stadium in one day

👶🏻 And most importantly, welcomed our Rivvy girl to the world!

2023 is gonna be a monster. Happy New Year everyone!!

In the spring of 2009, Ashley and I were two broke college kids who just started dating when we made the very wise and logical decision to spend every last dime we had to buy the maltese puppy Ashley always wanted.

We sold some of her jewelry to a pawn shop. I worked two jobs. Our families pitched in. Somehow, we scrounged up $550 in cash and took it to a breeder in Mansfield, Arkansas to pick up our sweet Emmy girl.

It’s impossible to describe the profound impact this dog had on our lives and our relationship from that moment on.

She was there when we fell in love, got married and had our two beautiful girls. She rode on Ashley’s lap when we moved our whole lives to California after college, and then rode shotgun with me from California to Texas.

She was there to comfort us through life’s hardest moments, and to celebrate the good ones. She was our best friend and part of our identity for an entire chapter of our lives.

On Wednesday, we made the incredibly difficult decision to close that chapter and let our Emmy girl cross the rainbow bridge.

Emmy, you took a piece of us with you to Heaven. Thank you for being the best dog in the whole world. We’ll never, ever forget you. ❤️🐾

MERRY CHRISTMAS! 🎅🎄 Staying up until 1:30am putting together toys is worth it 10 times over to see the look on their faces Christmas morning. My favorite day of the year ☺️

What. A. Year. 🚀

I’m so grateful to work with such a talented group of individuals who work around the clock to bring the most trusted entertainment to families around the world.

The video in the 2nd frame is my favorite moment of 2023. After months of planning and 3 grueling days battling high winds and every setback imaginable, we were down to our last hour of trying to make the world’s highest basketball shot from the top of the Stratosphere in Vegas before we had to call it quits. And then the impossible happened...and @matthewwmcb captured the raw reactions of @chadstagram1 and @tylerntoney right after the shot went in.

A few other stats and highlights from an unforgettable year for the @dudeperfect team:

-Accumulated 1.7 Billion views + over 100 Million hours (!!) watch time on YouTube

-Launched the Dude Perfect app and streaming service with over 1 million downloads in the first 3 months

-Made the World’s Highest Basketball Shot (856 feet!)

-Released a Dude Perfect toy line at the front of every Walmart in the country

-Completed a nationwide tour in 24 different cities with 200,000+ fans in attendance

-Set sail on the first ever (sold out) Dude Perfect CRUISE

-Bought a professional Pickleball team and joined ownership group in Premier League team, Burnley FC

-Hosted an alternate broadcast for two NFL games, including the first ever Black Friday game on Prime Video

-Played All Sports Tennis with Novak Djokovic

-Announced a first round pick at the 2023 NFL Draft

And even with all that, the most important highlight of 2023 was celebrating 10 years of marriage with the love of my life.

We already have some incredible things lined up for 2024 that I can’t wait to share. THANK YOU to everyone for the support. Trust me when I say, the best is yet to come for Dude Perfect! 👊

🙏 Husband and #GirlDad
